<% content_for :abstract do %>
		Agile is built on four fundamental principles or attributes - Communication, Simplicity, Courage and Feedback.  In this session, Rohit Bansal will talk about the importance of these attributes in our day-to-day work life, and their correlation with cognitive human behaviour. He will also discuss how Agile practices help people easily move between the increasingly divided worlds of thinkers and doers.
